Certainly! In MATLAB, there are several methods to determine the angle between two points on a Cartesian coordinate system. One common method is to use the atan2 function, which takes the difference between the y-coordinates and x-coordinates of the two points as input, and returns the angle in radians. Here is an example code snippet:
```
