### Response:
Here is a MATLAB code that can extract the top 3 most frequent flavor combinations from your chocolatier shop's sales records in a MySQL database:
```
% Connect to MySQL database
conn = database('database_name','username','password');
% Execute SQL query to retrieve data
sqlquery = 'SELECT flavor_emoji_1, flavor_emoji_2, flavor_emoji_3, sales_count FROM sales_records';
data = fetch(conn,sqlquery);
% Convert data to a table
sales_table = cell2table(data,'VariableNames',{'flavor_emoji_1','flavor_emoji_2','flavor_emoji_3','sales_count'});
% Create a new column for flavor combinations
sales_table.flavor_combination = strcat(sales_table.flavor_emoji_1,'-',sales_table.flavor_emoji_2,'-',sales_table.flavor_emoji_3);
% Get the frequency of each flavor combination
freq_table = tabulate(sales_table.flavor_combination);
% Sort the frequency table in descending order of frequency
freq_table = sortrows(freq_table,-2);
% Extract the top 3 most frequent flavor combinations
top_flavor_combinations = freq_table(1:3,1);
% Close the database connection
close(conn);
